records.addlTxt:
Defendant Richard W Kremer in court with attorney Jess Martinez.  Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 2, 3 and 4 are dismissed and read in.  Penalty enhancer on Count 1 struck by Court upon motion of the State.

The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld  Sentence of:
Credit - 0 days if revoked

Term of Probation: 3 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended (Court allows disclosure of Dr. Collins report dated 6-10-14);
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Tell each Doctor all prescriptions being taken including those other doctors are prescribing;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year or probation;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge

Buy Money: $225.00  to Waukesha Police Department  (to be paid at the rate of $25.00 per month commencing 11-4-2014)

Costs: $268.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00
(To to be paid as a condition of probation at the rate of $25.00  per month commencing 10-1-15).

Condition Time: 60 days Jail ( First 30 days STRAIGHT TIME last 30 days Huber NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS to include community service activites and volunteering) - Stayed and to be used at the agent's discretion.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
